# 5. 教室のセカイ

Saki: Wha—?! I don't recognize this school! How did we get here? We were in our own school's courtyard just a moment ago!
Ichika: I don't know... And it's eerily empty.
Ichika: You hear that? Cicadas. You don't usually hear them at this time of the year, right?
Saki: I hear something else, too. Someone playing guitar, and... singing?
Ichika: I may be imagining it, but it sounds like Miku.
Saki: You mean, someone's playing a Miku song?
Ichika: Sounds like it. Let's try to find them.
Saki: I think the sound is coming from over there.
Honami: Oh!
Shiho: !!
Saki: Hona and Shiho?!
Shiho: Saki... Ichika... What are you two doing here?
Ichika: We're...not sure how we got here.
Shiho: I see. Sigh. I'm going to be late for work...
Honami: Um, I also suddenly ended up here somehow. Then I ran into Shiho.
Honami: We don't know what's going on, but we heard singing, and decided to follow the sound.
Saki: We were thinking the same thing! Let's go together.
Honami: The singing was coming from this classroom.
Saki: H-Hello? Is anybody here?
Ichika: (This classroom seems familiar, as if I'd been here before. Ah, that's right. I dreamt about meeting Miku here.)
???: There you are at last! You sure kept me waiting.
Ichika: What?!
Miku: Welcome.
Saki: M-Miku?!
Shiho: What's this supposed to be?
Honami: Is this really Miku? No, it must be a projection, right?
Miku: Would you like to shake hands to see if I'm real? Here.
Ichika: I can...shake your hand?
Miku: It's good to finally meet you in person, Ichika.
Ichika: I can feel your hand! You're real!
Ichika: I saw you in a dream, and you looked just like this! I have so many questions!
Shiho: Me too. First of all, what is this place?
Miku: This is SEKAI, another world.
Ichika: Huh?
Miku: Welcome to your SEKAI!
Ichika: What do you mean?
Miku: It's a world created by your feelings.
Honami: How can that be possible?
Miku: SEKAI are molded by what's in people's hearts. Your feelings also weave together into songs here.
Miku: I'm sure some of the things you see here will seem familiar to you.
Shiho: I don't understand any of this. If this is some kind of a joke...
Shiho: Wait. What's my bass doing here? I didn't take it out of its case...
Ichika: My guitar is here too! It should be back in my room at home...
Saki: Look, there's a keyboard and drums too!  It's as if someone set everything up for band practice.
Saki: Speaking of which, I'd LOVE us to play together again!
Miku: Why not? You're welcome to use the instruments.
Ichika: What?
Miku: Isn't that what you wanted too, Ichika? To play as a band?
Saki: You're saying it's okay for us to play right here? That's awesome! Let's do this!
Honami: B-But... I promised a friend to meet her after school today.
Shiho: And I've got work. Besides, there's no song we'd all know well enough to play together.
Saki: There's one! That song we practiced together years ago!
Shiho: .....
Honami: Yes... I remember that one...
Saki: Then let's play it! We all know it, and it's not difficult!
Saki: Plus, it's one of Miku's songs, so it's appropriate!
Miku: Oh, it's something I sang? I'd like to hear you play it.
Saki: You hear that? How can you say no?
Saki: Ichi, aren't you up for it?
Ichika: Well... I...
Ichika: I want to try it. I think it'd be really nice to play that song together again.
Saki: See? Ichi wants to play too! Shiho, Hona, don't make me beg you!
Shiho: No, I'm leaving. How do I get out of this place? Miku, you must know?
Miku: Yes, of course. But I'm not telling you until after you've performed the song.
Shiho: What.
Miku: Hehe. You got me curious and now I want to hear how you play it.
Shiho: *Sigh* Well, if it's just one song.
Honami: ..... It's been a long time, so I may not be able to play very well, but I'll try.
Saki: Yay! Thank you!
Ichika: (I can't believe this is happening. We're really going to play together.)
Ichika: (And if that wasn't incredible enough, we're going to perform in front of Miku.)
Miku: Let's hear what you've got.
